<TITLE> 1 killed, 50 hurt in Narsingdi land dispute </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Narsingdi, March 6 (bdnews24.com)  One person was killed and fifty others were injured in an hour-long armed clash between locals over possession of a char, or river island, in Narsingdi on Saturday. The violence erupted at around 8am at Char Digholdi village, of the Sadar upazila, following a feud between local leaders Moslem Mia and Shawkat Ali over the land, police said. Narsingdi Sadar police chief Nazrul Islam said followers of the two set on each other with weapons to get hold of the char, a narrow strip of land rising from the Meghna River. The dead man, identified as Bacchu Mia, 40, was shot and died on the spot, Islam said. They injured were admitted to Narsingdi Sadar Hospital. Police have been posted at the char after the clash, Islam said. bdn
